commit.message:
Move locale check from import time to runtime

See #63.
Version 2.11
Fix #64: round before splitting into hours/minutes
Declare 2.10
Try fixing locale sensitivity under macOS.
Final tweaks for 2.9
Always round epoch to exactly the digits in a TLE
Explain epoch dates in the documentation
Fix `sat_epoch_datetime()` for ISS’s “December 32”

Fix #62 by letting epoch be retrieved as datetime

This restores the ability to access the value that the old 1.x
`Satellite` object offered as its `.epoch` attribute.
Replace days2mdhms() with one of our own
Fix indentation initially copied from C++ file
Fix incorrect indentation
For #62, remove "epoch" attribute from new Satrec

Fix #60 by advertising bstar as “/earth radii”

@Darkissuez points out that other sources, like the Celestrak FAQ
itself, dissent from the C++ comments and assert that this constant has
units of inverse Earth radii — and that only such units would in fact
fit its use in the formula.
Fix #61 by mentioning "ECI" and "ECEF" in docs
Update changelog and declare 2.8
Move `jday_datetime` to its own module

Add jday_datetime() to parse native `datetime`

Resolves #58 by merging.
Version 2.7
Clean up an awkwardly named test constant
Improve JD accuracy and simplify tests
Support passing positional arguments through “tox”

Remove “coverage” from tox.ini

I never use the coverage output, and it probably slows testing up a
little bit, so let’s remove it.

Get gravity constants working with sgp4init()

This should have taken fewer hours that it did.  The main confounding
factor was that the `twoline2rv()` setup and `sgp4init()` setup paths
can currently produce very slightly different values for `jdsatepochF`,
making only a very small difference to the output, but unfortunately a
difference that’s significant compared to the difference in gravity
model.  It took quite a bit of hunting to realize that of all the floats
in the structure that could be different, that was the important one.
By invoking the SGP4 routine with `sgp4_tsince()`, the tests are now
independent of any issues with Julian date offsets.

As you can see from the comments, there were other snags; the most
memorable was a `char` that was being set with a full 4-byte value,
overwriting the automatic next to it.
Fix: use the opsmode passed to sgp4init()
